<section id="deploy" class="relative py-32">
  <!-- Section border -->
  <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 right-0 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-border-subtle to-transparent"></div>

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6">
    <!-- Section header -->
    <div class="mb-16">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="text-accent font-mono font-bold text-lg">‚ü©</span>
        <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-accent uppercase tracking-widest">Deploy</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
        Two ways to run it
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary max-w-2xl">
        Managed gets you running in minutes. Self-hosted gives you full control. Either way, Baudbot runs on Linux and your code stays on your server.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Two-column cards -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

      <!-- Managed card -->
      <div class="relative rounded-2xl border border-accent/30 bg-bg-card p-8 flex flex-col">
        <!-- Recommended badge -->
        <div class="absolute top-6 right-6">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-accent/10 border border-accent/20 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-accent uppercase tracking-wider">
            Easiest
          </span>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-6">
          <div class="text-3xl mb-4">‚òÅÔ∏è</div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-3">Managed</h3>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            Sign up at <span class="text-accent font-mono text-sm">app.baudbot.ai</span> and we provision a Linux server for you, connect it to Slack through our broker, and handle the infrastructure. You skip the setup entirely.
          </p>
        </div>

        <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8 flex-1">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <span class="text-green-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">‚úì</span>
            <span>Server provisioned automatically ‚Äî nothing to install or configure</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <span class="text-green-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">‚úì</span>
            <span>Slack integration set up for you via the broker ‚Äî no need to expose your server to the internet</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <span class="text-green-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">‚úì</span>
            <span>Dashboard to manage your team, workspaces, and Baudbot instances</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <span class="text-green-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">‚úì</span>
            <span>Your code still runs on a Linux server you control ‚Äî not inside our infrastructure</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <a
          href="https://app.baudbot.ai"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="group inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-xl bg-accent px-8 py-3.5 text-base font-semibold text-bg-primary hover:bg-accent/90 transition-all shadow-lg shadow-accent/20 hover:shadow-accent/30"
        >
          Get Started
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5L21 12m0 0l-7.5 7.5M21 12H3" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Self-hosted card -->
      <div class="relative rounded-2xl border border-border-subtle bg-bg-card p-8 flex flex-col">
        <div class="mb-6">
          <div class="text-3xl mb-4">üêß</div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-3">Self-Hosted</h3>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            Run the install script on any Linux server you own. You wire up Slack yourself ‚Äî directly, or optionally via the open-source broker if you don't want to expose a public endpoint.
          </p>
        </div>

        <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8 flex-1">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <span class="text-green-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">‚úì</span>
            <span>Runs on any Linux server ‚Äî your hardware, your VPS, your cloud VM</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <span class="text-green-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">‚úì</span>
            <span>Full access to your dev toolchain ‚Äî compilers, CLIs, internal services, everything</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <span class="text-green-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">‚úì</span>
            <span>MIT-licensed ‚Äî fork it, extend it, run it forever without asking permission</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <span class="text-accent mt-0.5 shrink-0">‚Üí</span>
            <span>Slack setup is on you (or use the broker to avoid opening a public port)</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <a
          href="#quickstart"
          class="group inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-xl border border-border-subtle bg-white/5 px-8 py-3.5 text-base font-semibold text-text-primary hover:bg-white/10 hover:border-accent/30 transition-all"
        >
          See Install Docs
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5L21 12m0 0l-7.5 7.5M21 12H3" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Broker callout -->
    <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-border-subtle bg-bg-card/50 px-6 py-5 flex items-start gap-4">
      <div class="text-accent font-mono font-bold text-lg shrink-0 mt-0.5">‚ü©</div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          <span class="text-text-primary font-semibold">About the Slack broker:</span>
          {" "}Slack requires a public HTTPS endpoint to deliver events. Our open-source broker (a Cloudflare Worker) handles that for you ‚Äî Baudbot polls it over outbound HTTPS instead of opening an inbound port. Messages are end-to-end encrypted; the broker never sees your message content. The managed path sets this up automatically. Self-hosters can deploy their own broker or skip it and point Slack directly at their server.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
